    text: 'Soonmyung Paik and the National Surgical Adjuvant Breast and Bowel Project reported in the New England Journal of Medicine on 30 December 2004 that a 21-gene RT-PCR assay (the Oncotype DX Recurrence Score) quantifies the likelihood of distant recurrence in tamoxifen-treated, node-negative, estrogen-receptor-positive breast cancer, stratifying patients into low (6.8%), intermediate (14.3%), and high (30.5%) 10-year recurrence-risk groups.',
