        community: 'INSTITUTIONAL',
        occurredAt: '2006-10-11',
        datePrecision: 'DAY',
        reason: 'On the basis of the ECOG 4599 phase III data (presented at ASCO 2005), the FDA approved bevacizumab with carboplatin–paclitaxel for first-line non-squamous NSCLC, the first time an angiogenesis inhibitor was approved for lung cancer. The approval recorded the regulatory claim that adding anti-VEGF therapy to platinum doublet chemotherapy prolongs survival, while excluding squamous histology because of fatal pulmonary hemorrhage risk.',
